                    <h1 class="text-white">Philosophy, Vision & Mission</h1>
                    <p class="text-white mt-5 text-center">VISION & MISSION STATEMENTS</p>
                    <p class="text-white mt-5 text-center">
                            
                        Ina ng Buhay Catholic School (INBCS) envisions itself as a center for human and Christian discipleship where the learners trace the footsteps of Christ in their lives. Moreso, the learners are trained to upbuild a Christian community which is God fearing (Maka-Diyos), Patriotic (Makabayan), humane (Makatao), and environment- friendly (Makakalikasan). In gist, the school forms its students to become transformed individuals who live not for themselves alone but like Christ who lives for others.
                        Therefore, as a Catholic Institution INBCS is committed to:<br />
                        1. Promote the 5C’s (Competence, Compassion, Confidence, Commitment and Christianity);<br />
                        2. Strengthen religion as the core of the curriculum;<br />
                        3. Deepen the faith – life of the learners through the sacraments instituted by Christ and celebrated by the Catholic Church;<br />
                        4. Ensure Catholic formation inspired by the Blessed Virgin Mary, Mother of Life, and rooted in genuine faith and charity in serving others; and<br />
                        5. Provide programs and activities to develop learners’ talents, skills, creativity, & practice of the Christian Values; thereby, becoming an agent of the Church, touching the lives of the INBCSians, their families and neighbors.
                        

                    </p>
